  Learned that the heap is placed in CRAM.
  By reducing the task stack size, we have created about 2K byte more space
  in CRAM.

  With all the optimization, the max bandwidth that DPI can substain is about
  17 Mbps


11/13/01
  Tandberg has problem in hearing the audio of one of the HL encoder channels.
  But no audio buffer is detected.
  Other decoders work fine.

  When switching with that channel, lip sync will develop which will not be
  recovered.

  WCS set up discovers some issue when either network or the ad channel
  has no audio PIDs.

  When network has no audio PID, PPC will still send audio PIDs for ad,
  causing DPI to reset.  Edward has a patch to solve the problem.  For long
  term, we need to fix on PPC side.


11/14/01
  When network has audio but ad has not, DPI will reset.  Edward has another
  patch to fix this problem.


11/15/01
  Network has 2 audio PIDs, one is empty.  Noticed that when we have timeout,
  one audio PID is lost.  Eventually the next switch cannot be completed,
  causing a reset.

  Noticed that on two out of the 6 channels, we have several short ad.
  The 1st picture after switch is always the same number for the same
  channel.  This should not have been caused by bad arm time.
  Further study shows that about 100 to 200 TPs have been missing
  at the beginning of the ad.  Need to capture SeaChange ad server source
  to see who is dropping the TPs.

  Remaining two issues to be tackled after WCS:
    - why timeout cause audio PID to be dropped
    - why the beginning of ad is missing


