11/19/01
  Weekend test: no audio lipsync problem found.  No resets.

  Jim Clark on Cox:
    - Problem in DSP allocation:
      - Select no channels, but 6 DSPs, certain output rate.  Apply => OK.
      - Add channels.  Apply => DSP allocation error 25.
    - Need to support same input going to different output with different
      program number and PIDs mapping!
    - Problem starting with Rel 2.5:
      no longer can pre-allocate DSP numbers without selecting input.

  The Cox's problem is because Jim did not update the environment file.
  It is using the 2.3.8DP environment file on 2.4.9DP.  Since flash partition
  has been changed, the code is not correctly loaded to the DSP.

  Learned how to use the bootp server to update code:
    Need to point the bootp server to the appropriate ini file.
    In the ini file, need to specify the release directory.
    Since TFTP server will be used for actual data transfer, and TFTP requires
    a root directory, both the bootp ini file and the release directory must
    be under the same TFTP root directory.

  Tony's regression problem: seems he is using an old channel configuration
    which is no longer valid.  But still don't understand why this will cause
    the reset problem.  Will load debug code into his station for debugging
    since I cannot reproduce the same setup on my station.


