11/27/01
  - Consider combining monitor task, splice request task, and alarm task into
    one task to save CRAM space for task stack.


11/30/01
  - Noticed that for DPI=2 mode, if we pick more net channel than ad channel,
    that it will be stuck in a state that the switch always timeout.
  - Found out this has to do with the way we set the maxDelay of each channel.
    If a network channel is non-spliceable, then the maxDelay is set to 0.
    Therefore it will be very difficult to do a seamless switch into a
    non-spliceable network chennel.  Making the channel spliceable should
    solve the problem.


